The paper deals with two problems related to bin packing, which are classic topics in computer science and optimization. The first problem, bin packing with clustering, involves partitioning items into bins while taking into account their colors. This problem is related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are subfields of computer science. The second problem, online bin packing with delays, deals with packing items over time and minimizing the number of used bins and waiting costs. This problem is related to algorithms and optimization, which are also subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
